    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and Camshaft - Removal
        - Preliminary Checks
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s15.2.2" svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Preliminary Checks</title>
        <figure id="f3450015002" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM07/M07102.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Camshaft assembly gear backlash check (camshaft gear to crankshaft gear)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dial indicator with magnetic base</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft gear</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check and record camshaft gear backlash as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Mount
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_325.xml" xrefid="s15.t3">dial indicator with magnetic base</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s15.t3"/>
                    on rear of engine.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Position dial indicator tip on a gear tooth and remove lash by slowly turning camshaft
                    gear until all play is gone.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Turn gear back and forth by hand and read indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If camshaft gear backlash exceeds
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_323.xml" xrefid="s15.t1">specified limits</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s15.t1"/>, replace camshaft assembly.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450015003" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM07/M07103.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Camshaft end play</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reposition dial indicator and check camshaft end play as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Push camshaft to front of engine.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place a small pry bar between camshaft gear and crankcase and gently pry camshaft
                    forward. Compare dial indicator reading with
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_323.xml" xrefid="s15.t1">specifications</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s15.t1"/>.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If end play exceeds specified limits, replace camshaft assembly.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450015004" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM07/M07104.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crankshaft end play</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check crankshaft end play as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Mount dial indicator on lower crankcase assembly with indicator tip on end of crankshaft
                    gear as shown.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Move crankshaft forward with pry bar and zero the dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Move crankshaft back and forth while reading dial indicator. Compare dial indicator
                    reading with
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_323.xml" xrefid="s15.t1">specifications</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s15.t1"/>.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If end play exceeds specified limits, replace upper thrust bearing.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
